sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K625005
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: low to medium copy standard biobrick plasmid backbone
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Michael Eichenberger
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: psb4A5, but ORI exchanged with ORI of pSEVA 171

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: Suffix
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is the standard BioBricks suffix.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: TOPO
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Insertion of this site will enable generation of a TOPO vector. The vector will have a T overhang and permit binding of topoisomerase I for direct cloning of PCR products. See http://openwetware.org/wiki/Topoisomerase_I_mediated_TA_cloning for a complete description of Topoisomerase I mediated cloning. This site belongs 3' of the cloning site. It is the reverse complement of BBa_B0043.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: TSS
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part contains a stop codon in all 6 reading frames. Useful for ensuring that translation does not proceed through this part.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0054
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Terminator to be placed downstream of multiple cloning site in new pSB series plasmids. Similar to BBa_B0051.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:SequenceAnnotation.dcterms:title: identical to E. coli MG1655 between tonB and yciA

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: VR
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Reverse BioBrick primer annealing site (VR binding site)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the VR sequence to be used in construction of plasmids which include the VR primer site. It is the reverse complement of BBa_G00101.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
